title: AttributeError: 'CIFAR10' object has no attribute 'tgz_md5'
body_html:
My ENV:
Ubuntu 16.04.1 + Anaconda 4.3 (with Python 3.6)

Just testing dcgan, and my command line is as simple as:
python main.py --cuda --dataset=cifar10 --dataroot=....../cifar-10/cifar-10-batches-py

I got the following error messages:

(condaenv) pj@XXXXX:dcgan$ python main.py --cuda --dataset=cifar10 --dataroot=....../cifar-10/cifar-10-batches-py
Namespace(batchSize=64, beta1=0.5, cuda=True, dataroot='....../cifar-10/cifar-10-batches-py', dataset='cifar10', imageSize=64, lr=0.0002, ndf=64, netD='', netG=
'', ngf=64, ngpu=1, niter=25, nz=100, outf='.', workers=2)
Random Seed: 815
Traceback (most recent call last):
File "main.py", line 74, in
transforms.Normalize((0.5, 0.5, 0.5), (0.5, 0.5, 0.5)),
File ".../anaconda3/envs/condaenv/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torchvision-0.1.7-py3.6.egg/torchvision/datasets/cifar.py", line 38, in init
File ".../anaconda3/envs/condaenv/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torchvision-0.1.7-py3.6.egg/torchvision/datasets/cifar.py", line 140, in download
AttributeError: 'CIFAR10' object has no attribute 'tgz_md5'

Any suggestions?

Best Regards
Pei
